## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="641c4-102">Un'istanza di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> viene creato quando il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> oggetto genera il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object raises the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="641c4-103">Per ottenere informazioni sul risultato del riconoscimento, accedere il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> proprietà nel gestore dell'evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-103">To obtain information about the result of recognition, access the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property in the handler for the event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="641c4-104">Emulazione è il processo mediante il quale il testo, anziché l'audio, costituisce l'input per un motore di riconoscimento vocale.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-104">Emulation is the process by which text, instead of audio, is the input to a speech recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="641c4-105">Per ignorare gli input audio per un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> dell'oggetto durante emulazione, usare il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> (metodo).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-105">To bypass the audio inputs for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object during emulation, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="641c4-106">Se il motore di riconoscimento vocale rileva un'eccezione durante l'operazione di riconoscimento, la <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> viene impostata per l'eccezione e il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> è impostata su `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-106">If the speech recognition engine encounters an exception during the recognition operation, the <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> property is set to the exception and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property is set to `null`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="641c4-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> deriva da <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="641c4-108">L'esempio seguente aggiunge un gestore eventi per il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> evento da un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-108">The following example adds an event handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="641c4-109">Il gestore ottiene il testo riconosciuto dal <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> proprietà.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="641c4-109">The handler gets the recognized text from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.  
  sre.EmulateRecognizeCompleted += new EventHandler<EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs>(sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Handle the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.   
void sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted(object sender, EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  string phrase = e.Result.Text;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
